article.description: Ikenna Ndugba scored 14 points with five assists as Bryant narrowly defeated Dartmouth 64-60 on Saturday.
article.headline: Ndugba, Green lead Bryant to 64-60 win at Dartmouth
article.linkText: Ndugba, Green lead Bryant to 64-60 win at Dartmouth
article.story: HANOVER, N.H. -- Ikenna Ndugba scored 14 points with five assists as Bryant narrowly defeated Dartmouth 64-60 on Saturday. Michael Green III had 13 points for Bryant (8-4), which won its fourth straight game. Benson Lin and Mikail Simmons added 12 points each for the Bulldogs. Bryant put up 26 points in the second half, a season low for the team. Dartmouth (7-6) also struggled after halftime with 23 points on 29% shooting and missing all seven 3-point attempts in the half. Chris Knight had 21 points and 10 rebounds for the Big Green, Taurus Samuels added 13 points and seven rebounds. Aaryn Rai had 13 points and 10 rebounds. Bryant faces Maryland on the road next Sunday. Dartmouth matches up against New Hampshire on the road next Monday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
